The paper discusses a method for estimating the robustness of software performance in the face of uncertain parameters, which is a common problem in software engineering. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Polynomial Chaos Expansion (PCE) as a method for uncertainty propagation, which is a technique that is commonly used in the fields of programming languages (cs.PL) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. Finally, the paper uses case studies from different application domains, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
